                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4401: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-31T18:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 31—3:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consular corps to-day personally received assurances from Military Governor Wu
                    that order would be maintained Harbin and railway zone. He brought 1,000 troops
                    with him yesterday and 1,500 additional arrived this afternoon from Shanhaikuan.
                    He plans to send 5,000 troops against 3,000 mutineers and alleged brigands.
                    Harbin quiet but inhabitants worried. Legation informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
